children.text: The loose-fill ceiling insulation has not been restrained around the perimeter, which will allow it to move and reduce the thermal efficiency of the ceiling area.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 3900 Bulk Thermal Insulation states in section 5.3.4.1 that
‘Where loose-fill insulation is to be placed adjacent to ventilated or open eaves care shall be taken to avoid significant loss of insulation either during or after installation’.
The insulation needs to be fully restrained to achieve the required R-value across the entire ceiling area.
